@wagemann_modified
on-arrival: wagemann_plan_active = 1; economic_plan = 6; budget -= 4; unemployed -= 4.5; economic_growth += 0.22; workers_spd += 6*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 7*(1-dissent); left_dissent += 5; labor_dissent -= 3; dnvp_relation += 5; fiscal_stance -= 0.18; demand_impulse += 0.22; supply_impulse += 0.18; distribution_shift += 0.04; price_pressure += 0.07;

The Wagemann Plan is adopted with SPD-demanded modifications: mandatory union wages on public works, inclusion of housing construction for workers, protection of labor rights on all projects.

It's Wagemann's scale with WTB-Plan labor protections. The right-wing accepts because they need our support; we accept because massive stimulus helps workers regardless of ideological framing.

Employment surges, and this time workers benefit fully with decent wages and conditions. Our base appreciates that we extracted concessions rather than rubber-stamping a conservative plan.

@wagemann_rejected_conditions
on-arrival: wagemann_rejected = 1; dnvp_relation -= 5;

Our conditions prove unacceptable to conservative supporters. "The SPD wants to turn national mobilization into socialist employment programs!" they protest.

The Wagemann Plan dies because we demanded too much. Or perhaps it dies because conservatives were never serious about accepting labor's interests.

Either way, the stimulus doesn't happen.

@oppose_wagemann
choose-if: left_strength > reformist_strength + center_strength
unavailable-subtitle: The party lacks left-wing dominance to oppose a major stimulus plan.
on-arrival: wagemann_opposed = 1; left_dissent -= 10; labor_dissent += 5; dnvp_relation -= 8; workers_kpd += 2;

"The Wagemann Plan is nationalist economics disguised as recovery!" we declare. "It prioritizes heavy industry and ignores social priorities. We oppose this conservative program!"

Our left wing applauds the principled stand. But workers struggling with unemployment are confused: "The SPD opposes job creation?"

The KPD seizes the opportunity: "The SPD rejects jobs because they weren't socialist enough! Social fascism in action!"

[? if wagemann_plan_active = 1 : The plan proceeds without our support. When it succeeds in creating jobs, we look doctrinaire and out of touch. ?]

@demand_wtb_instead
view-if: wtb_adopted = 1
choose-if: left_strength >= 40 or labor_strength >= 60
unavailable-subtitle: We lack the strength to demand our own plan over Wagemann's.
on-arrival: wtb_demanded = 1; left_strength += 5; dnvp_relation -= 10;

"Germany already has a superior plan—the WTB-Plan!" we declare. "If conservatives now accept massive stimulus, they should accept our democratically-developed program, not a technocrat's conservative alternative!"

It's a principled stand for our own program. But it also sounds like petty jealousy: "Only our stimulus is acceptable!"

The coalition is unlikely to substitute WTB for Wagemann—we've created a stalemate where nothing happens.
